text.section:
The Department shall:
Identify and designate areas for public access to the waters of the State in each county that is located on the tidal waters of the State;
Coordinate with local and State agencies responsible for planning, purchasing, developing, and maintaining access areas;
Make recommendations to guide public agencies in the identification, development, and management of access areas; and
Serve as a repository for all information and inventories concerning shorefront access.
